cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper focuses on image classification using a deep learning network based on compressive sensing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning features from data using a cascaded compressive sensing network, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of a linear SVM classifier suggests the involvement of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments on the MNIST dataset, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
